#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an8.39"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an8.39:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 8 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 8 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.39:0.2"
msgid "4. Dānavagga "
msgstr "4. Giving "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 39. Abhisandasutta → puññābhisandasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an8.39:0.3"
msgid "39. Abhisandasutta "
msgstr "39. Overflowing Merit "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an8.39:1.1"
msgid "“Aṭṭhime, bhikkhave, puññābhisandā kusalābhisandā sukhassāhārā sovaggikā sukhavipākā saggasaṃvattanikā, iṭṭhāya kantāya manāpāya hitāya sukhāya saṃvattanti. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these eight kinds of overflowing merit, overflowing goodness. They nurture happiness and are conducive to heaven, ripening in happiness and leading to heaven. They lead to what is likable, desirable, agreeable, to welfare and happiness. "

msgctxt "an8.39:1.2"
msgid "Katame aṭṭha? "
msgstr "What eight? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.39:1.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako buddhaṃ saraṇaṃ gato hoti. "
msgstr "Firstly, a noble disciple has gone for refuge to the Buddha. "

msgctxt "an8.39:1.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamo puññābhisando kusalābhisando sukhassāhāro sovaggiko sukhavipāko saggasaṃvattaniko, iṭṭhāya kantāya manāpāya hitāya sukhāya saṃvattati. (1) "
msgstr "This is the first kind of overflowing merit … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an8.39:2.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako dhammaṃ saraṇaṃ gato hoti. "
msgstr "Furthermore, a noble disciple has gone for refuge to the teaching. "

msgctxt "an8.39:2.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyo puññābhisando … pe … saṃvattati. (2) "
msgstr "This is the second kind of overflowing merit … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an8.39:3.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako saṅghaṃ saraṇaṃ gato hoti. "
msgstr "Furthermore, a noble disciple has gone for refuge to the Saṅgha. "

msgctxt "an8.39:3.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyo puññābhisando kusalābhisando sukhassāhāro sovaggiko sukhavipāko saggasaṃvattaniko, iṭṭhāya kantāya manāpāya hitāya sukhāya saṃvattati. (3) "
msgstr "This is the third kind of overflowing merit … "

# NOTE: Curious that this isn’t in the fives.sc4pts-vp-pli4.246
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: appaṭikuṭṭhāni → appatikuṭṭhāni (bj)
msgctxt "an8.39:3.3"
msgid "Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, dānāni mahādānāni aggaññāni rattaññāni vaṃsaññāni porāṇāni asaṃkiṇṇāni asaṃkiṇṇapubbāni, na saṃkiyanti na saṅkiyissanti, appaṭikuṭṭhāni samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhi. "
msgstr "Mendicants, these five gifts are great, original, long-standing, traditional, and ancient. They are uncorrupted, as they have been since the beginning. They’re not being corrupted now nor will they be. Sensible ascetics and brahmins don’t look down on them. "

msgctxt "an8.39:3.4"
msgid "Katamāni pañca? "
msgstr "What five? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.39:3.5"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako pāṇātipātaṃ pahāya pāṇātipātā paṭivirato hoti. "
msgstr "Firstly, a noble disciple gives up killing living creatures. "

#. VAR: abyābajjhaṃ → abyāpajjhaṃ (bj, s1-3, mr) | avyāpajjhaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "an8.39:3.6"
msgid "Pāṇātipātā paṭivirato, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako aparimāṇānaṃ sattānaṃ abhayaṃ deti, averaṃ deti, abyābajjhaṃ deti. "
msgstr "By so doing they give to countless sentient beings the gift of freedom from fear, enmity, and ill will. "

msgctxt "an8.39:3.7"
msgid "Aparimāṇānaṃ sattānaṃ abhayaṃ datvā averaṃ datvā abyābajjhaṃ datvā aparimāṇassa abhayassa averassa abyābajjhassa bhāgī hoti. "
msgstr "And they themselves also enjoy unlimited freedom from fear, enmity, and ill will. "

msgctxt "an8.39:3.8"
msgid "Idaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamaṃ dānaṃ mahādānaṃ aggaññaṃ rattaññaṃ vaṃsaññaṃ porāṇaṃ asaṃkiṇṇaṃ asaṃkiṇṇapubbaṃ, na saṃkiyati na saṅkiyissati, appaṭikuṭṭhaṃ samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhi. "
msgstr "This is the first gift that is a great offering, original, long-standing, traditional, and ancient. It is uncorrupted, as it has been since the beginning. It’s not being corrupted now nor will it be. Sensible ascetics and brahmins don’t look down on it. "

msgctxt "an8.39:3.9"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, catuttho puññābhisando kusalābhisando sukhassāhāro sovaggiko sukhavipāko saggasaṃvattaniko, iṭṭhāya kantāya manāpāya hitāya sukhāya saṃvattati. (4) "
msgstr "This is the fourth kind of overflowing merit … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.247, sc5
msgctxt "an8.39:5.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako adinnādānaṃ pahāya adinnādānā paṭivirato hoti … pe … "
msgstr "Furthermore, a noble disciple gives up stealing. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.39:5.2"
msgid "kāmesumicchācāraṃ pahāya kāmesumicchācārā paṭivirato hoti … pe … "
msgstr "Furthermore, a noble disciple gives up sexual misconduct. … "

msgctxt "an8.39:5.3"
msgid " "
msgstr "This is the sixth kind of overflowing merit … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.39:5.4"
msgid "musāvādaṃ pahāya musāvādā paṭivirato hoti … pe … "
msgstr "Furthermore, a noble disciple gives up lying. … "

msgctxt "an8.39:5.5"
msgid " "
msgstr "This is the seventh kind of overflowing merit … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.39:5.6"
msgid "surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānaṃ pahāya surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭivirato hoti. "
msgstr "Furthermore, a noble disciple gives up alcoholic drinks that cause negligence. "

msgctxt "an8.39:5.7"
msgid "Surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭivirato, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako aparimāṇānaṃ sattānaṃ abhayaṃ deti averaṃ deti abyābajjhaṃ deti. "
msgstr "By so doing they give to countless sentient beings the gift of freedom from fear, enmity, and ill will. "

msgctxt "an8.39:5.8"
msgid "Aparimāṇānaṃ sattānaṃ abhayaṃ datvā averaṃ datvā abyābajjhaṃ datvā, aparimāṇassa abhayassa averassa abyābajjhassa bhāgī hoti. "
msgstr "And they themselves also enjoy unlimited freedom from fear, enmity, and ill will. "

msgctxt "an8.39:5.9"
msgid "Idaṃ, bhikkhave, pañcamaṃ dānaṃ mahādānaṃ aggaññaṃ rattaññaṃ vaṃsaññaṃ porāṇaṃ asaṅkiṇṇaṃ asaṅkiṇṇapubbaṃ, na saṅkiyati na saṅkiyissati, appaṭikuṭṭhaṃ samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhi. "
msgstr "This is the fifth gift that is a great offering, original, long-standing, traditional, and ancient. It is uncorrupted, as it has been since the beginning. It’s not being corrupted now nor will it be. Sensible ascetics and brahmins don’t look down on it. "

msgctxt "an8.39:5.10"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhave, aṭṭhamo puññābhisando kusalābhisando sukhassāhāro sovaggiko sukhavipāko saggasaṃvattaniko, iṭṭhāya kantāya manāpāya hitāya sukhāya saṃvattati. (5–8.) "
msgstr "This is the eighth kind of overflowing merit … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an8.39:6.1"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, aṭṭha puññābhisandā kusalābhisandā sukhassāhārā sovaggikā sukhavipākā saggasaṃvattanikā, iṭṭhāya kantāya manāpāya hitāya sukhāya saṃvattantī”ti. "
msgstr "These are the eight kinds of overflowing merit, overflowing goodness. They nurture happiness and are conducive to heaven, ripening in happiness and leading to heaven. They lead to what is likable, desirable, agreeable, to welfare and happiness.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an8.39:6.2"
msgid "Navamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

